value.0: Hello. A pleasant and profitable day to you, <mister/missus>.
Do you have my note of payment from the blacksmith in Osthavn?

Yes, yes, here you go. Oh, and thanks for the excellent work.

*He flashes you a toothy smile*

That was a thousand in total. Less 200 in expenses, taxes, duty, bonds, insurance, brokerage fees, customs fees, guild dues, port charges, dock charges, export certificates, import certificates, and certificates of certification. 

Then you get half of what's left.

Well, you could, I'm sure... but there'd probably be a court filing fee of 100 crowns, 150 crowns for the booking, another 200 for the judge, taxes, deposition fees, 50 for the clerk, another 50 for the archivist...
Do you have my note of payment from the blacksmith in Osthavn?
But of course. Do you have any other questions?
Captain Lowrance down at the docks knows these waters like the inside of an ale cup. He should be able to get you there in practically no time.
Ah, you're back. Do you have the iron ore you said you'd get?

Oh... that's -all-?

*He looks at the ore, apparently disappointed*

It's not a lot, but I suppose it will have to do. Now I'll need you to take it to the blacksmith in Ostland so we can collect our profit.
I didn't?
Oh, I'm sure I said -something- about it to you. I told you we'd split the profit evenly, didn't I? Now, there can't be any profit if we don't sell the ore first, right?

I'm glad you see it my way. It's quite simple, really, and not dangerous at all. You just need to take this ore to the blacksmith in Osthavn. That's in the Jarldom of Ostland on the east side of the big island of Ruathym. He'll give you a note of payment. You bring that back here to me and you'll get your pay. 

*He gives a toothy smile*

No trouble at all, right?
Certainly. Any other questions before you go?
Captain Lowrance down at the docks knows these waters like the inside of an ale cup. He should be able to get you there in practically no time.

If you feel you must do that, then you go right ahead. I'll just point out that the Jarl is a busy man with a short temper, and he hates to be interrupted with false claims. Remember, you agreed to split the profit with me, and so far there hasn't been any profit. So, you see, I've done nothing wrong and I don't owe you anything... and I -won't- owe you anything unless you take that ore to Ostland and get it sold for us.

So, are you going to complain to the Lord of Wiltun?
Ah, hello again! Have you returned with the ore you were supposed to get from Caraigh?

It's on the isle of Caraigh, as I said. If you talk to Loriano outside the keep, he might be able to drop you off at the southern docks. The mine itself is not too far north of there. Just look for a big hole in the ground, heh heh.

Oh! Hello there, <mister/missus>. 

*He rubs his hands together and smiles toothily*

I expect you've come looking to earn a bit of coin, eh?
Oh, simple, really. I'm just looking for a few adventurous souls to help me gather some iron ore from the Jarl's mines on Caraigh.

Oh, heavens, no. This is all perfectly on the up and up. 

*He produces an official-looking document*

You see, I have a permit from Master Parrico himself allowing me to collect from the mines. For a fee, of course.

Well, I figure - since the mine is a bit of a dangerous place, what with the local goblins - I'll split the profit with you evenly. That's after I pay the taxes and such, of course. Depending how much iron ore you're able to bring back, we might be able to clear as much as a thousand crowns.

If you talk to Loriano outside the keep, he might be able to drop you off at Caraigh's southern docks. The mine itself isn't far north of there. Just look out for a big hole in the ground... 

*he chuckles, quite amused with himself*

Oh, no more than a minor nuisance, I'm sure. From the information I've been able to put together, they've just scared off the regular miners. Which gives -us- a nice opportunity to earn a bit of coin for ourselves...

*he winks conspiratorially*

... if you're brave enough to take the job, that is.
Yes, I have, and here it is - now where's my pay?
What? Only 400 gold? I thought you said a thousand?
Fine, fine...  I suppose it wouldn't do me any good to complain to the Jarl, would it?
Right... I got it. Never mind.
No, not yet. I'll be expecting my payment in full when I return with it, though!
Yeah, what's the best way to get to Osthavn?
All right, then. I'll see you again soon.
Yes, I found some in the mines there. Here you go.
Whoa, wait a minute! You didnt say anything about going to Ostland!
No, you didn't. Now where's my pay?
Hmph. I suppose not. So what do I have to do to get my pay, now?
I'll be back as soon as I get that note, and I'll expect my pay then.
